<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-10-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1239" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1239">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1215/374.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mexican Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 510.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 12, 1911.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: The memorandum<note n="3" xml:id="d1239fn3">
                                <ref target="frus1911#pg_604">For Rel. 1911, pp. 604</ref>–<ref target="frus1911#pg_605">605</ref>. The memorandum under
                                acknowledgment is that of October 6, 1911.</note> of the Department
                            of State, replying to that of this Embassy dated September 12,
                            concerning the Chamizal award, was received today.</p>
                        <p>I am communicating its contents to the Ministry of Foreign Relations and
                            am awaiting instructions before addressing your excellency again on the
                            subject.</p>
                        <p>Meanwhile I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilberto Crespo y Martínez</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>